1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill Nos. 3068 & 3049, Page 39, Section
2 589.417, Line 27, by inserting after said section and line the following:
3
4 "660.845. 1. (1) There is hereby created in the state treasury the "Missouri Crime
5 Victims Fund", which shall consist of moneys appropriated by the general assembly and any
6 gifts, contributions, grants, or other donations from any public or private source. The state
7 treasurer shall be custodian of the fund. In accordance with sections 30.170 and 30.180, the state
8 treasurer may approve disbursements. The fund shall be a dedicated fund and, upon
9 appropriation, moneys in this fund shall be used solely as provided in this section.
10 (2) Notwithstanding the provisions of section 33.080 to the contrary, any moneys
11 remaining in the fund at the end of the biennium shall not revert to the credit of the general
12 revenue fund.
13 (3) The state treasurer shall invest moneys in the fund in the same manner as other funds
14 are invested. Any interest and moneys earned on such investments shall be credited to the fund.
15 2. Moneys in the Missouri crime victims fund shall be disbursed to entitlement
16 jurisdictions, eligible entities, or local governmental entities that are eligible for victim
17 assistance grants under the federal Victims of Crime Act, Pub. L. 98-473, and related
18 regulations, and such jurisdictions and entities shall use such moneys for the same purposes as an
19 entitlement jurisdiction, eligible entity, or local governmental entity may use victim assistance
20 grants under the federal Victims of Crime Act, Pub. L. 98-473, and related regulations."; and
21
22 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
23 accordingly.
